</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[813,1452,434,842]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[813,918,434,458]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Britski, Birindelli, Garavello" baseAuthorityYear="2012" box="[937,1199,434,458]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Anostomidae" genus="Megaleporinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="piavussu">
<emphasis box="[937,1199,434,458]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Megaleporinus piavussu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was identified as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Valenciennes" baseAuthorityYear="1836" class="Actinopterygii" family="Anostomidae" genus="Leporinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="obtusidens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">L. obtusidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Graca, Pavanelli" box="[964,1214,466,490]" firstAuthor="Graca" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="58 - 64" refId="ref84115" refString="Pavanelli CS, Graca WJ, Zawadzki CH, Britski HA, Vidotti AP, Avelino GS, Verissimo S. Fishes from the Corumba Reservoir, Paranaiba River drainage, upper rio Parana basin, State of Goias, Brazil. Check List. 2007; 3 (1): 58 - 64." type="journal article" year="2007">Graça, Pavanelli (2007)</bibRefCitation>
. Ramirez 
<emphasis box="[1321,1375,466,490]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">et al.</emphasis>
(2016) described the new genus, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ramirez, Birindelli, Galetti Junior" authorityYear="2016" box="[1068,1223,498,522]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Anostomidae" genus="Megaleporinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1068,1223,498,522]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Megaleporinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and proposed the new combination. 
<bibRefCitation author="Britski" box="[956,1167,530,554]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Britski" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="441 - 75" refId="ref79344" refString="Britski HA, Birindelli JLO, Garavello JC. A new species of Leporinus Agassiz, 1829 from the upper rio Parana basin (Characiformes, Anostomidae) with redescription of L. elongatus Valenciennes, 1850 and L. obtusidens (Valenciennes, 1837). Pap Avulsos Zool. 2012; 52 (37): 441 - 75." type="journal article" year="2012">
Britski 
<emphasis box="[1035,1090,530,554]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">et al.</emphasis>
(2012)
</bibRefCitation>
redescribed 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Valenciennes" baseAuthorityYear="1836" box="[1304,1451,530,554]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Anostomidae" genus="Leporinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="obtusidens">
<emphasis box="[1304,1451,530,554]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">M. obtusidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and described the new species, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Britski, Birindelli, Garavello" baseAuthorityYear="2012" box="[1135,1259,563,586]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Anostomidae" genus="Megaleporinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="piavussu">
<emphasis box="[1135,1259,563,586]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">M. piavussu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(under 
<taxonomicName box="[1339,1442,563,586]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Anostomidae" genus="Leporinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1339,1442,563,586]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Leporinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) from the upper rio 
<collectingRegion box="[1011,1080,594,618]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Paraná</collectingRegion>
basin. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Britski, Birindelli, Garavello" baseAuthorityYear="2012" box="[1156,1407,594,618]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Anostomidae" genus="Megaleporinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="piavussu">
<emphasis box="[1156,1407,594,618]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Megaleporinus piavussu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished by having 39 or 40, rarely 41, pored scales in the lateral line, and mouth terminal, except in some large adults with somewhat subterminal mouth (
<emphasis box="[1256,1284,691,714]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">vs.</emphasis>
41 to 43, rarely 
<quantity box="[813,865,722,746]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1176" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" unit="in" value="44.0">44 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Valenciennes" baseAuthorityYear="1836" box="[872,1016,722,746]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Anostomidae" genus="Leporinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="obtusidens">
<emphasis box="[872,1016,722,746]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">M. obtusidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and mouth directed somewhat or entirely downward in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Valenciennes" baseAuthorityYear="1836" box="[953,1096,754,778]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Anostomidae" genus="Leporinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="obtusidens">
<emphasis box="[953,1096,754,778]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">M. obtusidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The epithet 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Britski, Birindelli, Garavello" baseAuthorityYear="2012" box="[1237,1326,755,778]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Anostomidae" genus="Megaleporinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="piavussu">
<emphasis box="[1237,1326,755,778]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">piavussu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to the common name of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Garavello, Britski" baseAuthorityYear="1988" box="[1047,1239,786,810]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Anostomidae" genus="Megaleporinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macrocephalus">
<emphasis box="[1047,1239,786,810]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">M. macrocephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
“ 
<emphasis box="[1260,1434,787,810]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">piavuçu, piaussu</emphasis>
”, but these are different species and should not be confused.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
